fields.description:
Location, Location, Location.... as they say.

    Well you would be hard pressed to beat this one !

    Its all here at your doorstep... literally :-)

    Easy access - stroll to everything !

    You will find yourself stepping out and strolling to everything - everywhere - every day. Also easy cab access day and night. Ferry, train or bus options also.

    Whether here for business or pleasure - this is the perfect Sydney 'base'.

    Gorgeous, private, Rocks Village setting. Far enough away from the main tourist hub at Circular Quay to keep it  close enough to enjoy the vibe.

    The Boutique part of the new Rocks/Harbour foreshore precinct !

    Huge selection of Harbour Side Restaurants, Cafes and Bars, Historic Pubs - Shops... all at your doorstep. No more than a 1 min stroll.

fields.context: This is a well equipped, very comfortable apartment --- the host has thought of everything.... all the kitchen equipment imaginable.  The apartment is very convenient to the old city, cathedral, museums, and restaurants.  Works very well for a family - clean, well kept, plenty of room and bathrooms.  Our host, Paul, was very responsive to us and very helpful.  Convenient grocery store, close to the river for walking.  There is a convenient bus for getting to central station for day trips in Belgium.  This was a very enjoyable experience.

This is a very nice appartement. We really liked the the modern interior of the appartement. It's a clean, pleasant and very comfortable place to stay. 

We could park our car in the private indoor parking place and hired our bikes just around the corner.

Paul is a great host. It was a pleasure to stay in this apartment.

Regards,

Marcel

The appartment is beautiful, the best I've ever been in on Airbnb. Clean, huge, light, beautiful furniture, fantastic view, best location. I can really recommend this flat.

Additionally Paul was a very good host, prepared us with all important information, good tips, did answer immediately and was very helpful. 

Our trip just couldn't have been better! Thanks Paul!

fields.context:
Enjoyed an excellent time in Antwerp. 

The apartment, it's location, and Paul's helpful tips, were all top class. 

I would recommend this apartment highly. 

Regards, 

Brian

Fantastic trip to Antwerp!

Staying in Paul's apartment near the MAS museum was a brilliant experience for the 4 of us. He is a super host; very helpful and friendly. He's put together lots of information in the apartment about great local restaurants around the docks and there is loads of detail about Antwerp as a whole.

The apartment is exactly as wonderful as the photography on the Airbnb site. It's a good big size with lot's of light through the floor to ceiling windows.

Both bedrooms are gorgeous with super comfortable beds and all the furniture and fittings are very cool with everything you could want for a short or longer stay.

The apartment is in a great location in the regenerated docklands area around the MAS museum - which is only 2 min walk away. It's only 10-15 min walk into the old quarter of Antwerp and we were actually in the Zuid area (Contemporary & Fine Art museums etc.) within a 30 min walk - all very easy. The apartment is only a 5 min taxi ride from the Centraal station too.

Very highly recommended apartment & host - book with confidence!

Wij hebben met ons driehellon een volle week genoten van ons verblijf in het appartement. Deze is zeer ruim, schoon en met voldoende privacy voor een ieder vanwege de twee badkamers en gescheiden toiletten. Het is prettig dat er ruim voldoende badhanddoeken aanwezig zijn. Indien nodig kan de wasmachine zelfs gebruikt worden! De ligging is perfect. Vanaf de snelweg is het zeer makkelijk te bereiken en het hebben van een plek in de parkeergarage is super. Het is een rustige buurt, met toch ook veel gezelligheid en centraal gelegen. Dicht bij twee musea, tal van restaurants, op slechts 15 minuten loopafstand van het oude centrum. Paul Zeguers is zeer gastvrij, heeft ons rustig en duidelijk alles over het appartement en omgeving uitgelegd. Een pluspunt is dat je tegen een zeer geringe vergoeding gebruik kan maken van onder andere Nespressocups, wijn, bier, en frisdrank: handig als je iets vergeten bent en de winkels zijn dicht. Wij kunnen dit appartement aan iedereen aanbevelen.

Beautiful and spacious apartment with great interior in a lovely and hip location.
Very nice contact and simple key handover. The hosts are very nice and the apartment has all the comfort. Thank you very much, we had a great stay and Antwerp is such a nice city.

Great flat in a very nice area of Antwerp. Host was very helpful and easy going. Definitly recommend staying here to anyone. 

Flat was very clean, very spacious and well equiped. Drinks in the fridge and coffee were offered for a small contribution.

Paul's apartment is excellent. The place is clean, spacious, modern, and in a trendy area of Antwerp. Check in was easy and Paul is very responsive to any messages. I would recommend this place to anyone.

fields.context: Paul and Gina greeted us and told us about the apartment and the area and made us feel very welcome. We arrived a little bit early and we were able to park our car and get settled in the apartment. We truly loved our experience and highly recommend Paul and Gina as hosts and their beautiful apartment in a very trendy area near the water as a perfect place for a vacation in Antwerp!

Paul was fantastic! I emailed him late at night for a co worker that was in Belgium and needed a place to stay last minute. Paul responded quickly and answered all of my questions. The apartment was just as described, clean, and in a nice area. Will definitely be contacting Paul again next time I need a place to stay in Antwerp!

Paul was already at the apartment when I arrived so no waiting around outside. He efficiently and quickly showed me around the apartment without being too fussy. I felt completely at ease immediately. The apartment was perfect for exploring Antwerp with perhaps a ten minute walk into the centre of town. But if you don't wish to go into town there are plenty of bars, restaurants, cafe's bakeries within a very short walk of the apartment. The views from the apartment make it feel pretty special, even at night but when the curtains are drawn you have your privacy. The major boon with this apartment is the car parking. Parking a car in Antwerp is a trial sometimes but here no. Underground, very secure parking with access into the apartment block. A lot of Airbnb apartments are lived in by their owners which of course is mostly the point with this service. I do however prefer 'Pure Lets' without all the personal items of the owners surrounding you. This apartment is purely let for guests so no clothing in the wardrobes etc. A great place to stay with a decent road network in and out to the apartment too. Perfect.

fields.context: Mooi en groot appartement op een goede locatie. Vriendelijke en behulpzame verhuurder. Zeker een aanrader!

An absolutely fantastic place. I have no hesitation in recommending this flat and it's gracious host. The location is great at the north end of the city centre, easy to find and has a variety of artisan shops and galleries on the doorstep with a very handy mini-market right downstairs.

The flat immediately impresses with views, and the security of the entrance. The lift is small but can still fit 2 people & suitcases. 

The decor is neutral and spotlessly kept, in fact the whole flat was immaculate, with quality furniture throughout.

The listing could really do with a layout to really sell it. The living space and 2 bedrooms are far enough apart that noise isn't an issue. There is a useful office space. The 2 balconies are a useful addition to the space. Our party was 2 couples and we did not feel cramped or as if we were tripping over each other.

The kitchen is extensively kitted out with everything you need to either eat on the fly or host a diner party. The large fridge meant that we only had to shop once for our stay leaving us all the sightseeing time to enjoy.

Wir sind  von dieser Wohnung total begeistert! Sie ist nicht nur super-schhellon und komfortabel, sondern auch perfekt ausgestattet. Alles war extrem sauber, die Betten sind sehr bequem. Die Wohnung liegt in einer ruhigen Seitenstrahelloe; die Schlafzimmer liegen auhelloerdem hinten am ruhigen Innenhof. Die Lage war fhellor uns optimal. Das Hafenviertel direkt vor der Hausthellor bietet eine grohelloe Auswahl an sehr schhellonen und guten Restaurants, Cafes, Kneipen u.s.w. Das MAS ist 50 Meter entfernt. Bis zur Kathedrale im Zentrum lhellouft man 15 bis 20 Minuten. Eine der vielen Fahrradstationen lag direkt um die Ecke.
Die Vermieter waren sehr freundlich und hilfsbereit. Alles lief reibungslos.

fields.context: Lovely, very comfortable apartment in a great neighborhood.

This is a great apartment that I would, and have already, recommend to friends. The welcome was warm and everything explained clearly. The owners are a great team and even Paul's daughter kept me up-to-date and informed. The apartment is spacious, modern (yet cosy) and, above all, super clean and uncluttered. The situation is perfect - quiet yet with a great atmosphere and reasonably close to the city centre.

Paul and Gina are amazing hosts - everything was perfect, from the initial communication about the stay to check out. 
The apartment is fantastic - it's even better than on the pictures. Totally new and has everything you need for comfortable stay - from Nespresso coffee machine to shampoo. Excellent location - amazing harbor view, supermarket next door, lots of restaurants and just 15-20 min walk from the historic center. 
Definitely will recommend this place to friends and will stay there again if I go to Antwerp. 
Paul and Gina, thanks a lot!

fields.context: Het appartement van Paul ligt op een geweldige plek, is schoon en van alle gemakken voorzien. Perfect om een weekend of langer in Antwerpen te verblijven. Parkeren onder het appartement erg gemakkelijk en ook de supermarkt in de straat is ideaal. Een aanrader!

Wij hebben een heerlijk verblijf gehad in het appartement van Paul en Gina op het Eilandje in Antwerpen. Het appartement is prachtig. Het is schoon, gezellig en alles wat je nodig hebt is aanwezig. Paul en Gina zijn zeer vriendelijk en gastvrij. Wij komen graag in Antwerpen en dit appartement zullen we dan ook zeker nog eens boeken.

We hebben een zeer aangenaam verblijf gehad in het appartement van Gina en Paul. Het appartement is ruim, schoon, goed onderhouden en erg gerieflijk ingericht. Het zicht op het water en de flanerende mensen vanaf het balkon is erg leuk. 
De ligging van het appartement is ideaal. De directe omgeving biedt veel mogelijkheden om uit eten te gaan, een terrasje te pakken. Einde van de straat het MAS waar je 's avonds van het prachtige uitzicht over de verlichte stad kunt genieten en op loopafstand van het centrum. Ideaal is ook dat je je auto onder het appartement in de garage kunt stallen. Kortom een appartement waar we graag terug willen komen. Gina en Paul, hartelijk dank voor jullie sympathieke ontvangst.

fields.context: We had a wonderful few days in this apartment. It is in a great location with lots of great restaurants and bars nearby. The centre of town is an enjoyable 20 minute walk away. The apartment is beautifully furnished and the beds are very very comfortable. A great experience and we will definitely be back.

Binnen minuten ontmoetten we eigenaar Paul. Vriendelijk en behulpzaam. Hij leidde ons de garage binnen en hielp met de koffers naar boven te brengen. Zijn uitleg over het gebruik van het appartement was helder en kernachtig. Ook waren de bijzonderheden goed gedocumenteerd. Bij de documentatie behoorde ook een uitleg over de directe omgeving van het appartement.

Het appartement is ruim van maat en zo ook de afzonderlijke ruimten. Direct valt het op dat alles kraakhelder en schoon is. Badkamers en toiletten hygihellonisch en blinkend schoon, royaal voorzien van handdoeken. Mooie beddenbedekking en zalige bedden. Keuken is compleet en fijn dat er een vaatwasser en Nespressomachine was met een assortiment koffiecupjes. Je bereikt het appartement per lift. Betaald parkeren belast niet gezien de ruime plek in de garage.

Aangenaam zijn de twee balkons. Die aan de woonkamer vangt de ochtendzon en die aan de werktafel de namiddagzon. De isolatie is perfect: bij gesloten schuifdeuren is het prettig stil. Direct naast de ingang is er een kleine maar goed gevulde supermarkt en heel dicht bij een superbakker met heerlijk brood. We hebben daar fijn ontbeten. Restaurants alom en het stadshart is op 2 kilometer.

Ik zal het appartement zeker aanbevelen bij vrienden die Antwerpen willen aandoen en voor onszelf houden we het adres en telefoonnummer van Paul bij de hand.
Die Wohnung ist absolut perfekt. Paul hat sich wunderbar um uns gekhellommert, alles erklhellort und sehr viele wichtige und interessante Informationen vorbereitet gehabt.

fields.context:
Die Wohnung war fhellor uns (zwei Paare)perfekt. Sie ist sehr geschmackvoll und zweckmhellossig eingerichtet, hat sogar zwei Badezimmer und wir fhellohlten uns sehr wohl hier. Paul hat uns sehr herzlich empfangen und uns viele Informationen zur Umgebung gegeben. Die hellobergabe und die Abgabe der Wohnung war unkompliziert und hat super geklappt. Die Lage nahe beim Hafen (Start der Hafenrundfahrt gleich um die Ecke) und doch nur ca 15. Minuten zu Fuss zum historischen Zentrum war optimal. In unmittelbarer Nhellohe gibt es gute Restaurants und Einkaufsmhelloglichkeiten sowie eine Velostation als Teil eines helloberaus praktischen Mietsystems, mit dem man  die Stadt sehr flexibel erkunden kann. Auch wenn man mit dem Zug anreist ist die Wohnung direkt vom Bahnhof aus mit dem Bus sehr einfach zu erreichen.
Eine sehr empfehlenswerte Adresse fhellor einen gemhellotlichen Aufenthalt in Antwerpen!
Herzlichen Dank Paul & Gina fhellor eure Gastfreundschaft

Reinhart & Verena, Gaby & Jhellorg (Schweiz)

Heerlijk weekend in Antwerpen met vriendinnen. Een fijn ruim apartement, om de hoek bij het bijzondere MAS en tal van leuke restaurants en cafeetjes. Bakker, Supermarktje en krantenkiosk op struikelafstand. En je zit zo in het oude centrum.

Wij hebben een superweekend gehad in dit mooie appartement. Het is fijn gelegen, in de buurt van leuke tentjes. Het appartement is ruim en schoon en voldeed helemaal aan onze verwachtingen. Bovendien verliep de communicatie soepel en werden wij warm onthaald. Een absolute aanrader!

fields.context: Perfect, again!

Spent a week at the apartment while in town for work.  Can't say enough about it.  The location worked our great.  Was about a 15 minute drive to the harbor area where I worked.  The bonus was when I came back in the evening.  It was just a short walk into the city center with lots of places to eat and see the sights.  Gina was there to let us in and show us the facilities and give us advise about things in the area.  I would absolutely recommend this apartment to anyone considering it and will be checking its availability the next time I return for work in the area.

My second time staying in one of Pauls apartments and nothing has changed in either the experience or the apartments. Both the first and third floor apartments offer equal comfort. 

Private indoor parking, decent supermarket next door, the nicest bakery across the road and short walk to town. Nothing to dislike.

fields.context: Onze eerste ervaring met airbnb was gelijk een hele goede! We zijn zeer vriendelijk ontvangen door (schoon)mama, die ons uitleg gaf over het appartement en de omgeving. Het appartement was brandschoon en van alle gemakken voorzien. Wij vonden het een fijne plek om te verblijven en hebben genoten van ons weekend.

Wat een heerlijk appartement! We hebben vaak tegen elkaar gezegd: Zou hier zo kunnen wonen. Gelegen in een trendy opkomende buurt. Fantastische bakker om de hoek, Espresso-bar en gezellig kroegje aan de overkant. Auto kon geparkeerd worden in het pand en via de sluisbrug aan het MAS zit je met 10 minuten lopen in het historisch centrum van Antwerpen. Paul ontving ons heel hartelijk en liet ons achter met de nodige tips. Absolute aanrader!
Very comfortable and nice apartment! I would definitely stay here again.

fields.context:
Wij zijn eind februari 2017 in dit prachtige appartement te gast geweest. Je bent echt te gast in dit luxe ingerichte appartement dichtbij alles waarvoor je naar Antwerpen gaat. De woonkamer is groot en toch gezellig, de open keuken is van alle gemakken voorzien. Een goed Nespresso apparaat helpt bij het wakker worden. Zo ook de meer dan  lekkere douche. Het aparte bad (in badkamer 1) is ook veelvuldig gebruikt. Wij hebben Paul als gastheer getroffen en voelden ons meteen thuis. Voor extra vragen of wensen is Paul altijd bereikbaar en behulpzaam om te helpen. 
Vlakbij is een meesterbakker gevestigd waar je goed kan ontbijten. En voor lunch of diner is er in de directe omgeving erg veel keus uit zeer goede restaurants. Voor een goede kop koffie kan je aan de overkant terecht. De stad is snel te bereiken met Velo Antwerp, een soort witte fietsen systeem. Echt geweldig. 
Kortom, houdt je van modern en een hippe uitdagende wijk? Dan moet je hier zijn! Maar niet allemaal, wij willen namelijk wel vaker gaan.

Een ontzettend mooi appartement, op loopafstand van de oude binnenstad, de locatie is een hippe maar wel rustige wijk van Antwerpen met alle voorzieningen die je nodig hebt, een bezoek aan het museum MAS met het panorama terras is zeker een aanrader, daarnaast wil ik Paul ooppk bedanken voor zijn flexibiliteit waardoor wij op zondag op een later tijdstip het appartement konden verlaten. Wij gaan dit appartement zeker weer boeken als wij in Antwerpen zijn.
Perfect appartement en locatie. Heerlijke bedden en alles in orde. Fijne uitvalsbasis voor Antwerpen.

Overall, the unit is exactly as described in the listing, and is actually *better* than it appears in the photos. We will 100% stay here again when we're back in Antwerp. Sitting on the front balcony for sunrise and/or sunset was my favorite part of my days while visiting. The kitchen is incredible, everything is well furnished and well maintained. Not to mention there's a parking spot included!

To reiterate - 100% amazing, would definitely stay here again and recommend to anyone :)

fields.context:
to start with Muriel was a fantastic host, giving us perfect directions on how to find the apartment, letting us store our bags there as we arrived earlier than check in time & helping us with maps & directions on places we needed. The fridge was stocked with goodies for breakfast, some fruit, some water and even a couple of local beers which was a nice touch thanks.

The apartment itself could not have been in a better position, it overlooks a beautiful square with cafes and a little pub perfect for a drink in the afternoon sun, and its a 3 minute walk from the big main church & the main square where you will find 1000 places to eat drink and go partying. Inside the apartment its great a big comfy bed in the bedroom and a large couch in the lounge room that folds out into another large double bed, a little balcony, a good size kitchen, and a shower and toilet which are both seperate which is a great plus if you are traveling with a few people like us.

If you need somewhere in Antwerp you cant go pass this apartment & Muriel is a fantastic host so you cant go Wrong...

Absolute great location, and Muriel is an extremely friendly host. We had flexible check-in and check-out times, and the location of the apartment could not have been better (close to cool shops, nice cafes and the city center). Very nicely decorated apartment! If you're thinking about going to Antwerpen, definitely think about renting this apartment!
We 've had a great stay over at Muriel's place. Cosy clean, well put together and located in the very centre of Antwerp.

We will try to make the story brief. We met Muriel on Monday afternoon, and she was utterly charming and interested in showing us the details of the apartment. She was concerned since we were more than two that we would need more towels, and she delivered them when our other guests arrive. The location of the apartment is so central and fantastic. The space is very much as the pictures depict. The view is lovely, and the square - which is the view - offers many interesting restaurants and bar/cafes. Our only issue was that the shower was simply not able to be adjusted with any subtlety. The options were very hot, and, one notch below, cool. We were there for a week and no one said it was satisfying. After leaving Antwerp for Berlin, we tried to stay in this apartment for a couple of nights but it was unavailable. We would obviously stay there again.

The pictures shows a flat looking nicer, much bigger and newer than it is, but basically the place ok. The view is on a small place in the historical center.
But we had a bad experience as we found the toilets very dirty and had to clean up before using it!! ... nothing that disgusts me more...
Nevertheless, the rest was clean.
The owner seem a gentle person, but this experience is not what I expect at Airbnb as its obvious that it is just a way for the owner to earn money, nothing to do with a home experience. For this price in Belgium you find really much better. I would prefer an hotel.

Amazing location!!! it really is in walking distance from everywhere and the cafe downstairs is lovely.

The apartment is well depicted in the photos. We were 4 adults and one 2 year old and we fit fine in the apartment even if it is not that big. The shower was a bit tricky but nothing bad. The kitchen is actually quite large. The apartment was perfectly clean.

We really liked that the heater is a gas stove in the living room which gave a nice atmosphere to the apartment. 

Miertje was very friendly and helpful and we are especially grateful for the flexible check-out time! 

The only thing that bothered my husband a bit was noise in the evening and noise from the cafe...the building is old and the walls thin - you can hear people going up the stairs and the music that is played in the cafe downstairs (very softly). The cafe closes early (8pm) so that really is not a bother but I guess we were just unlucky as there was music until very late both Friday and Saturday nights coming from somewhere else... Me and my 2-year old slept right through it but my husband found it annoying. 

Still, overall, I would recommend the apartment to any of my friends and I would gladly stay there myself again too.

    Well you would be hard pressed to beat this one !

    Its all here at your doorstep... literally :-)

    Easy access - stroll to everything !

    You will find yourself stepping out and strolling to everything - everywhere - every day. Also easy cab access day and night. Ferry, train or bus options also.

    Whether here for business or pleasure - this is the perfect Sydney 'base'.

    Gorgeous, private, Rocks Village setting. Far enough away from the main tourist hub at Circular Quay to keep it  close enough to enjoy the vibe.

    The Boutique part of the new Rocks/Harbour foreshore precinct !

    Huge selection of Harbour Side Restaurants, Cafes and Bars, Historic Pubs - Shops... all at your doorstep. No more than a 1 min stroll.

fields.context:
Die Wohnung ist totel niedlich und supersauber. Die Lage ist umwerfend mitten in der Altstadt. Geschhellofte, Kneipen, Museen und zahlreiche Sehenswhellordigkeiten- alles fuhellolhelloufig super zu erreichen. Auch der Fluss ist nur einen Minispaziergang weit weg.
Sehr netter und unkomplizierter kontakt. Kann ich nur weiter empfehlen.

Ein sehr gemhellotliches stilvolles Apartment direkt am schhellonen Vrijdagmarkt in der historischen Altstadt gelegen. Sehr zu empfehlen!
Tolle Cafes, Kneipen, Restaurants und Sehenswhellordigkeiten in direkter Umgebung.
Unkomplizierter und netter Kontakt, vielen Dank!

Great apartment- Simple with everything you need (host provided lots of extras). Comfortable beds, fantastic location for exploring the city. Would definitely return. Flexible, helpful and friendly host.

fields.context: Miertje's apartment is spacious and nicely decorated. Its location is great, very central and close to interesting museums and the Cathedral . There are nice cafes around the area.

My stay on this appartment was excelent! When we arrived she was already waiting us. She explained everything very well and was very gracious. The appartment is very nice, the internet connection worked well, which is important to me, and there are a lot of towels, which is good as well! The appartment is very well located. I really liked this appartment and I'm sure I will stay on it when I come back to Antwerp. Miertje is very nice and I recommend her as your host.

We had a wonderful stay in this enchanting apartment in the heart of Antwerp. The pictures on airbnb give a realistic impression. Miertje's welcoming us was warm and friendly, and we could easily get in touch with her upon arrival and departure time. The place overlooks a charming old town square and everything's very, very close by: cafhellos, restaurants, grocerie shops, a delicious bakery, thrift shops and and and. Even though the flat is super centrally located, the neighbourhood is not very loud. We would book this apartement again in a sec - and I'm looking forward to do so :)

fields.context: Wij hadden een hele fijne ontvangst en heerlijk verblijf nabij het bruisende centrum van Antwerpen.

Aanrader! Miertje biedt een fijn en sfeervol appartement van alle gemakken voorzien in hartje Antwerpen op loopafstand van veel. Met zijn tweehellon is het voldoende ruim. Met 3 of 4 personen zou ook kunnen, er is een bedbank. Van het onderliggende cafhello hadden wij geen last - onhoorbaar, sluit om 20u - er is hooguit wat reuring op straat, maar dat heb je overal in het midden van de stad. Ghellohellon ontbijt, wel een goede bakker en een super om de hoek. Desgewenst heeft Miertje tips over wat er te zien en te doen is.

Miertjes apartment made our stay in Antwerp perfect! It was sooo comfy. There was everything we needed :-) The oven kept us warm :-) Also the key-handover worked out perfectly. All in all: A wonderful apartment for a wonderful visit to Antwerp!

fields.context: Nice and very clean appartment, excellent location. We stayed here with four girls and had a great time.

Miertje kindly waited until almost midnight for us to get into the city, and when we arrived we found the apartment clean, pretty and with a great location. It was a pleasure to stay here and I hope to come back one day.

This is a wonderful property. We are a fit couple about 50 y.o. each, and love to shop for food in foreign countries and cook it ourselves. We love coffee, quaint living rooms and playing Scrabble. We LOVE being centrally located, and not have to take a bus or subway to get to the quaint and historic. If THIS resonates with you, then Miertje's property is for you! There isn't much to complain about, and there's MUCH to praise! The bottom line is that we had a great time and have no regrets! We were in a quiet apartment, with loads of natural light, in the heart of historic Antwerp, surrounded by coffee shops, Museums, historic squares and interesting shops.  I'll start with whatever I can think of that fell short a bit: 1) The apt. is one just flight up from the street, but the steps are steep and narrow. This cuts both ways, actually. If you want the Building Code of 21st Century America, don't bother going to Europe altogether - particularly the historic districts! This wasn't a deal breaker by any stretch, but be ready to take your luggage up one piece at a time (advice: travel light!) 2) Could Miertje invest in the shower, and make it a bit more luxurious, instead of just average? I don't exactly know what her expense overhead is, but I guess she could. 3) I wish it was just a bit cheaper to rent in late January, but that's Europe, there ARE heating expenses, and it's a competitive marketplace! More than that, I can't think of anything even questionably bad to say! The apartment was 100% clean. There were a good 20-30 new towels. No laundry, but we didn't need any. The kitchen was fine, with loads of things that made life easier (utensils, coffee, salt, pepper, etc). A mixture of antiques and IKEA, everything was just right for a couple looking for a romantic weekend in historic Belgium. We got to know Miertje a bit when we arrived at around 20:30 pm. Miertje is an artsy, creative person who lived in the US for a few years in the '80s. She's a pleasant, happy humanist, with obviously great EQ. She was not in our hair, we didn't see her again, and she even let us "check out" by ourselves at 7 AM, simply by leaving the keys in the apartment and pulling shut the door from the street! Miertje lives in a different neighborhood, so we weren't running into her A gruff landlord can ruin a mood, and we didn't have that experience!
In short, if you want elevators, the hum of vacuums and room service - check into a Marriott! If you want an authentic historic "local" experience in Antwerp - this is The Genuine Article! I'D DO IT AGAIN, EXACTLY THE SAME WAY!

fields.context: Het appartement op de Vrijdagmarkt in Antwerpen is een fantastische keus voor een weekendje weg in deze heerlijke stad. Het is supernetjes en schoon en erg centraal gelegen. Miertje was erg gastvrij en behulpzaam. We verbleven er met vier volwassenen wat betekent dat er twee mensen in de huiskamer op de slaapbank moeten slapen maar dat was absoluut geen straf! Heerlijke bedden, schone handdoeken en superkoffie, alles goed geregeld.
Clean, neat, warm and safe place right in the centre of Antwerp. Nice owner, everything went smoothly.

There is no better place for getting to know Antwerp than Miertje's perfect little place in the middle of the old center of the city. Everything can be reached by simply walking through the wonderful streets of Antwerp. The apt. itself is directly above a wonderful cafe which was not noticeable throughout our stay of 6 days (Try their African ginger tea, it is delicious). Miertje is a wonderful host full of good advice. She gave us a warm welcome and with her resourcefullness she also gave us a good first orientation. The apt. is just as described and it looks out on the Vrijdagmarkt which is a very relaxed little space within the liveliness of the old centre. We will gladly come back!

Leuk appartement aan plein in het hartje van Antwerpen met huurfietsen (Velo) om de hoek. Sfeervol ingericht en in de keuken en badkamer is werkelijk alles aanwezig wat je maar nodig kunt hebben. Voor verbetering vatbaar: de gordijnen in de slaapkamer. Die waren erg dun zodat het straatlicht ons wakker hield. Een (verduisteringen)-rolgordijntje zou hier geen kwaad kunnen. Verder prima plek!

Miertje was goed te bereiken en erg vriendelijk. Omdat het allemaal zo goed beviel zijn we zelfs nog een nacht extra gebleven.

fields.context: Location was terrific - really couldn't be faulted.  Right in the heart of the old city nearby the cathedral, yet quiet and relaxed in the evenings. Plenty of cafe's, restaurants and bars are very close by and Miertje is a lovely host providing more than is really necessary in the apartment which is snug and nicely furnished. The bed is also really comfy!  But there isn't a washing machine and the nearest laundry is some way off.  Nevertheless a lovely stay and would certainly consider it again.

We hebben een heerlijk weekend gehad in dit appartement. De locatie is top, met een mooi uitzicht op een gezellig pleintje. Het appartement is ruim en van alle nodige gemakken voorzien. Groot pluspunt: goede bedden dus we hebben erg lekker geslapen. Het enige minpuntje was de geluidsoverlast van de bovenburen. Maar dit kon de pret niet bederven. Miertje heeft goed voor ons gezorgd tijdens ons verblijf, er stonden zelfs boodschappen en verzorgingsproducten klaar voor gebruik! Wij komen zeker nog eens terug.

Amazing stay!! Miertje was very welcoming and gave great advice.  Flat was beautiful, clean (even better than the photos!); everything we could possibly want - including things for breakfast!  Location really central but also quiet.  Would definitely stay again!

fields.context:
Miertje was responsive, helpful and very understanding. Mutual respect goes a long way! Her cosy and clean flat is indeed located in great part of the city, we can really recommend it. Even though it's right on top of a stylish cafe, it's not annoyingly noisy during the day, and the evenings are quiet. 

Fantastic host! She even goes out of her way proving great coffee(!), milk and toiletries/towels, more than one could ask for.

Miertje hat lange auf uns warten mhellossen, weil wir durch den Orkan in Deutschland nicht in Deutschland abfahren khellonnen. Sie hat uns herzlich empfangen. Alles war perfekt, viele Informationen hellober Antwerpen, Tipps, wo wir essen gehen khellonnen, die Wohnung liebevoll bis ins Detail eingerichtet, Kaffee, Tee, Milch und viele Lebensmittel standen zur Verfhellogung, die Khelloche bestens eingerichtet, das Bad sehr geschmackvoll, Whellosche vorhanden. Die Lage ist gut, in der Nacht ruhig, sehr zentral. Nur zu empfehlen.

We cannot recommend Miertje's Antwerp apartment highly enough! Even better than the pictures. Perfectly located for exploring Antwerp, spotlessly clean, lovely bedding, plenty of towels and well stocked kitchen, fridge and pantry. Miertje is a pleasure to deal with and goes above and beyond for her guests. 5 stars!

Unfortunately the apartment wasn't in a quiet part of town. There was a constant noise coming from the cafe/restaurant downstairs. No loud music or anything but it just felt like sour portent was in the middle of the cafe and we couldn't relax because of it.

It was in a convenient location walking distance to everything so that was a plus.

It was very over priced for what it was and not what we had expected, mostly because of the constant noise from downstairs which didn't stop until 11:45 one evening.

The apartment was tidy and mostly clean, but both my Mother and myself ended up with red blotchy bite marks all over out bodies which we suspected were bed bugs as the bedding for the double bed wasn't fresh and the sofa wasn't ideal either. 

We couldn't relax the whole time we were there and just had to make the best of it.

Sadly I can't recommend it.

The host was very friendly and sociable though, we got a very warm welcome.

De locatie van het appartement is perfect; middenin het oude centrum en op loopafstand van het openbaar vervoer. Het appartement was precies zoals op de foto's en bovendien erg schoon. Miertje was a wonderful host and her apartment is full of charm and character. It was warm and cosy, the bed was very comfortable and the shower piping hot. There was absolutely nothing we needed; the fridge was stocked with food, there were maps and guides and everything was catered for. We were incredibly impressed. It's on the best part of the center, still close to the Meir (for those interested), but smack in the middle of all the nice vintage, antique shopping streets. 
The apt was spotless, fully equipped kitchen with basic breakfast amenities (granola, butter, jam etc), shower with enough shampoo etc., clean towels and lots of books/tourist info plus even some games in the living room. The apt is above a bistro, but since it closes at 9pm or so, we didn't have any noise problems. 
Loved this apt so much, will book this one straight next visit. Thanks Miertje for making our stay easy and pleasurable!

The apartment is on the corner of Frijdagmarkt in the very center of Antwerp, above the "In de Roscam" Cafhello. The best neighborhood in town for shoppers and people interested in culture and museums.The Plantin-Moretus Museum is only 50 meters away from the location. A definite recommendation for Antwerp visitors!!!

We loved the stay. Location is just a 5 minutes walk from the Cathedral and Groete Markt. Miertje was waiting for us and explained all the details around the house and also about the location. She recommended that we must visit MAS, and she was so right. It was a very nice touch that she had coffee, butter, jam and even some apples in the fridge. One flight of stairs was not bad except at night when it was a bit dark. Wifi worked flawlessly.

fields.description:
Location, Location, Location.... as they say.

    Well you would be hard pressed to beat this one !

    Its all here at your doorstep... literally :-)

    Easy access - stroll to everything !

    You will find yourself stepping out and strolling to everything - everywhere - every day. Also easy cab access day and night. Ferry, train or bus options also.

    Whether here for business or pleasure - this is the perfect Sydney 'base'.

    Gorgeous, private, Rocks Village setting. Far enough away from the main tourist hub at Circular Quay to keep it  close enough to enjoy the vibe.

    The Boutique part of the new Rocks/Harbour foreshore precinct !

    Huge selection of Harbour Side Restaurants, Cafes and Bars, Historic Pubs - Shops... all at your doorstep. No more than a 1 min stroll.

fields.context:
We absolutely loved this apartment; it is in a charming square, which although has 4 or 5 bars in is still fairly quiet at night, but also really close to lots of interesting areas of Antwerp. Great for all sorts of shopping, restaurants, bars and sightseeing.
The restaurant downstairs was a particularly nice and friendly place to hang out (and closed by 9/10 pm, so no noise issues).
Miertje was easy to deal with and all plans for access etc. were well handled. She was also helpful and informative about places to visit.
The apartment is spotlessly clean and comfortable, and lots of little extras provided made for a very pleasant stay.
 We will be back.
Leuk appartement aan een gezellig pleintje. Hartje Antwerpen!

This is a very cute apartment in a perfect location. Miertje was a great host, taking time to point out things to do and places to go on a map when we arrived. She also has some books about Antwerp to give us more ideas.

fields.context:
Ik verbleef 2 nachten met mijn vriend in Kristien haar appartement, waar we het alleen maar fijn hebben gehad. Het uitzicht is mooi, je kan de kerkklokken horen spelen in de verte en 's nachts is de kerktoren die je door het raam kan zien prachtig verlicht. Het is een rustige buurt, maar tegelijkertijd ben je midden in het centrum. We zijn 3 dagen gebleven en hebben alles te voet gedaan:  zonder moe te zijn aan het eind van de dag. 
Kristien zelf was snel met reageren op berichten die ik heb gestuurd, ook tijdens mijn verblijf. Ik kan dit appartement en deze gastvrouw zeer aanbevelen.
Perfect location

The apartment is on a quiet corner above a small open market square.  It has a balcony and windows that overlook the square, which is quite charming.  Downstairs the owner has run a cafe for about 15 years, so guests do not have far to go for really delicious light food.  The cafe does not open early or close late, so there is no issue with activity downstairs during sleeping hours.  Everything in the apartment worked well and I would not hesitate to stay there again.  Kristien was a fine host and runs the cafe so is available if need be.

De wijk vind ik zelf een van de leukste van Antwerpen. Gezellig aan een pleintje waar overdag van alles gebeurd, maar savonds en in de vroege ochtend heerlijk rustig. Goede uitvalsplek waar je heel Antwerpen kan ontdekken en even langs kan wippen voor wat tassen droppen. Goede tips, welkom ontvangst en geen probleem om tas te laten staan met uitchecken.

Die Wohnung ist super gemhellotlich. Die Lage ist perfekt und Kristien super freundlich. Die Nachbarn hhelloren gute Musik, vielleicht ein bisschen zu laut. Das Cafhello unter der Wohnung ist toll und hat nachts geschlossen, somit kann man sehr gut schlafen. Bei unserem nhellochsten Besuch whellorden wir wieder dort wohnen.

Not only does Kristien's apartment look the same as it does in the photos, but it's BETTER in person. It's so quaint and the location is idyllic. When you stay here, you feel like you're a part of the community. Plus, it was extremely clean, something I'll admit I was a little surprised at. I would expect an apartment of this age to be a little dirty but it truly was incredibly clean. 

The bed was comfy, the pillows fluffy, and the Aesop products aren't just for the photoshellothey're actually there IRL for you to use.

The *only* thing I would suggest being aware of is that the little square where it's located can get a touch noisy on a Friday morning or on Saturday nights. As the square is a community gathering space, it's completely understandable and 100% did not impact my enjoyment of the space. But if you are someone who is sensitive to noise, it may bother you. 

Last thing: My absolute favourite part of the whole experience was sitting at the little cafe downstairs for a glass of wine and a little snack.  I'll be telling anyone I know that's going to Antwerp to look up Kristien's apartment. If you stay here, you won't be disappointed.

Ik zou hier zeker naar terug gaan als ik nog eens in Antwerpen zou verblijven!

Tinne's apartment is a tastefully decorated spacious place. It is in a very central location, close to the main train station as well as to many nice restaurants. Tinne was out of town when we visited, and were greeted by her wonderful mother who was extremely helpful and caring.

We will be sure to check availability of this apartment first, during our upcoming trip to Antwerp.

The apartment was perfect, and Tinne was a great host. The apartment is very spacious, and through the massive windows we had a spectacular view of the park. The location is quiet and the amenities are excellent. Would definitely come back.

I've a lovely time at Tinne's apartment.. It was beautifully decorated and conveniently located. Tinne was a great host and we spent an afternoon together visiting the museum and galleries and just spending time together. Tinne's mom, Mimi was great too! She met me at the train statiion and showed me to the apartment. She even gave me great tips on food places!

fields.context: The Apartment was very big and clean. We had a wonderful sight over the Park and a very comfortable doublebed. The Apartment is at a very central location so that we could easily walk into the center. Tinnes very friendly mom helped us out finding very good restaurants. We will definitely check availability the next time we come to Antwerp ( Very nice city!!!)

The appartment is at a very convenient location, right at the Stadspark and close to the Theater and shopping streets. Central Station is a 15 minutes walk away. There are bicycles via Antwerpen-Velo in the same street, which makes it very easy to get around. To find out how to make use of the bikes, go to (Website hidden by Airbnb) The appartement is very spacious en light. Tinne was not there during our stay, but we were greeted by her mum, who was very friendly and gave us several sightseeing tips. Only two minor negative points: one of our nights we did not sleep so well because of mosquito's and noisy neighbours upstairs. Just bring some repellent and earplugs and you will be fine. I can definitely recommend this appartment for a nice stay in Antwerp.

Tinne was a perfect hostess and she even picked us up from the train station. Het apartment is big, clean and perfectly located next to the city park. During the weekend it really felt like home. I defintely recommend this one!

fields.context: I stayed one month in Tinne's home. It  is fine, the park view is amazing and stuffs are in good condition in living room and kitchen. You can find almost everything you need but I had some communication problem with Tinne as she is in America. I have told her that I would extend my stay (before moving), I just had to see home but she has already rented home to next guest one week after I moved to apartment. Also you should pay special attention for neighbors if you'll live in this house. fields.context: Fantastic spot

The apartment is very spacious as the photos show, and everything was clean and comfortable. There are two small elevators (the apartment is on the 7th floor) and a washer but no dryer (a clothes drying rack is provided - we found that it took 2 or 3 days for clothes and towels to dry). The kitchen is well-equipped with everything you need, and the bathroom facilities include a separate toilet-room in the entry hall. There's a nice, deep bathtub which was great for soaking in after a long days of walking around. The separate shower tends to send water all over the bathroom floor - we found that it helped to remove the grate from over the drain to help it more easily catch all the runoff. The train station is a bit of a walk (15 to 20 minutes depending on pace) and we thought the major tourist areas like the Grote Markt are more of a "take a cab" distance than a walking one, but we were there in winter when the weather didn't make walking very appealing. Taking the train to Brussels, Ghent and Amsterdam were fun and easy. Antwerp is a great home base for exploring the area, and this apartment is a great place to come home to.
Great flat near the central station and the city centre as well. The hosts were very helpful without being intrusive. The rooms were very spacious and the kitchen was well equipped.

It's located in a quiet neighborhood outside the center, and Marleen's restaurant recommendations (within 10-15 min by foot) were spot-on. fields.context:
I booked Marleen's apartment for my parents, who came to visit me in Antwerp. From the start, communication with Marleen was great. She was quick to reply and very accomodating.
Due to a miscommunication we were a little late to pick up the keys, but Marleen was very understanding. She made my parents feel at home immediately and even gave them some home-made jam!
The apartment itself is spacious, comfortable, nicely decorated and clean. My parents stayed for three nights and enjoyed it very much. They slept really wel: it is a quiet neighbourhood and at night there is no noise from outside. As for the location, I can testify for myself (I live closeby) that is perfect to discover Antwerp. Either by bike, by foot or by public transport. Moreover, there are some nice cafhellos, restaurants, (grocery)shops and parks nearby. 

My parents told me that when they will be back to visit me, they would love to stay at Marleen's again!

Marleen was friendly and welcoming!

fields.context: Staying with Fronk & Lieve was my very first airbnb experience and they were wonderful hosts to one of the most beautiful and exciting cities in the world. Their place was very easy to access from Antwerp Centraal train station and were a lot of fun to hang out with as well as being mindful of the travellers space. The view from the bedroom is amazing and is perfect for unwinding after a days activities. Both open and wonderful people, I now consider them friends and would highly recommend a stay at their place to anyone thinking of going to Antwerp.

Fronk and Lieve were all my best friend and i could have asked for. We were tired after six hours of trains and walking around hostile Brussels when we begged (not literally) for them to take us in. Less than an hour after our plea for help, they graciously accepted our request. Though our frazzled brains got lost on the way, Fronk and Lieve welcomed us with dinner and suggestions for places to visit. Both are kind, generous, and very smart. They will share stories and smiles and knowledge as long as you are willing.  Fronk and Lieve made an unexpected part of our trip feel like home. They understand you may need your space, but at least one is always available to help. If we are ever in antwerp again, we will definitely stay with them.

fields.context: Fronk & Lieve are really nice hosts and I had a good stay in their pink room, which was spacious, with a very comfortable bed, and an amazing view over Antwerp rooftops from the room's balcony. The room is at the back of the apartment away from the street so is nice and quiet. There are external blinds for the windows which were great as I like a dark room for sleeping in. It's easy to get to town from their apartment - a short bike ride (on the bike they kindly lent me) or 10-12 minute walk to Antwerp Central station, or the No.10 tram. Fronk & Lieve shared stories with me about Antwerp's history which made my visit to the city a much richer experience, and made some great recommendations on things to see and places to eat. Thanks again Fronk & Lieve!

fields.context: I spent a couple of nights with these guys, and they are super easy going. The apartment is located very close to the station, where I understand the town center begins: well, it's a nice walk through a quite international (mainly Arab) neighbourhood, but you can easily get the bus. Or, much better, you use Fronk&Lieve's bicycle!! I went everywhere biking and it's been so much fun! Also, most of the town you would explore by biking is flat, so it is really easy. Fronk&Lieve gave me great hints about sites to explore, clubs and restaurants (do not miss a fish Tajine at the Moroccan restaurant El Wardi !). A plus is the market, do not miss it. Thanks

The apartment is well located, close to the center and the railway station.
I can recommend this place!

fields.context:
First of all I must say that staying in Borgerhout is probably the best way to get to know Antwerp: the neighborhood reflects the changes of the whole city in the last decades, and in the same time it is really near to the historical center and to most of the places you would wish to visit.
But the real added value of this accommodation are the hosts. Fronk and Lieve are that kind of people who have a real experience of life and the world, and use it to be open to and respectful of those they meet. Their house is not only a place, but a real hub connecting people. It's been a beautiful experience to stay in Antwerp for the first time living at their place.

I had a lovely stay with Fronk and Lieve, they were so helpful with any questions I had about where to go for food or anything, and took time to be interviewed for my project, and were overall really interesting to talk to. The room I stayed in was a good size, plenty of space, and a fantastic view out of the window. Very easy to get to from the train station, and plenty of options for eating out nearby.

Zeker aan te raden!

fields.context: I really enjoyed staying at Fronk & Lieve's place.  It was only a short walk from Antwerp Central, but far enough off of the beaten path to make for a quiet night's sleep.  The main historic district was only about a 20 minute walk or a 5 minute tram away, so Fronk and Lieve's flat was the perfect mix of proximity and tranquility.  Lieve was extremely responsive, especially given my last minute request.  As a first time airbnb'er, I felt quite comfortable in Lieve and Fronk's flat and enjoyed my short stay.  Great people, great city, great price - thanks for making my first airbnb experience a positive one!

De verhuurders, Fronk en Lieve, zijn aardige en behulpzame mensen. Zij waren op de afgesproken tijd aanwezig en maakten ons wegwijs in Antwerpen. De locatie van het appartement is centraal en de buurt is prima. De prijs concurreert wel met hotels. De kamer en badkamer waren echter niet wat wij verwachten voor deze prijs. Beiden konden beter voor deze prijs.

As Fronk and Lieve's place was full, they arranged for me to stay with Marleen. Marleen's beautiful house is located close by and also within walking distance to central station. Marleen was accommodating and a great host.

fields.context: Lieve is a wonderful woman who helps Pieter running this airbnb. The room is very nice and the hosts help you with everything you need. It's not too far from the city center. I would definitely recommend this!

Lieve's place was full but she very kindly organised for me to stay with her friend, Leyes in her beautifully restored 19th century home. 

Conveniently, Lieve allowed me to leave my bags at her place while I explored the city on my first morning in town - she even provided me with an umbrella. This woman would do anything to make sure you had a lovely stay in Antwerp; I felt so lucky to encounter such a generous and caring host - she really made my trip special. 

Staying with Leyes was an absolute pleasure! Her place was airy, very clean and comfortable. Leyes clearly put a lot of effort in to making sure that my stay went well which I very much appreciated. Leyes very generously offered breakfast and we had a very interesting and thoughtful discussion about the current state of Belgian politics - it was definitely a highlight of my trip. I'm so glad I got to experience the hospitality of Lieve and Leyes and I thoroughly recommend both hosts to the airbnb community!

Because Fronk & Lieve are on holiday, the boyfriend of her daughter, Maxime, welcomed me to the nice and spacious flat. It was an excellent stay. Maxime was always very nice and helpful and made me feel at home at once. The room is cosy, clean and quiet, and this in middle of town. Excellent stay! I highly recommend this place!
Thanks very much, Maxime!
Just sad, that I couldn't meet Fronk an Lieve, who must be very nice and interesting people too.

Nous avons hellothello trhellos bien accueilli ! Lieve a hellothello trhellos sympathique et nous a donnhello de trhellos bonne adresses pour le weekend et des conseils de visites.
La chambre hellotait simple mais trhellos agrhelloable pour la seule nuit passhelloe hello Anvers.

Fronk answered my mails quickly and informative. He told me before the reservation that the room I selected is not available, but they can offer me another room in the building on the same comfort level. Unfortunately I didn't get any pictures about the offered room before the reservation, but I reserved the room.

I wrote the time of my arrival in advance. Finding of the place wasn't a problem, it's quite near to the Central Station. The neighborhood is not the best of Antwerp but it's okay for the price. There are a lot of public transport opportunities on the street of the place that was useful for me. 

Lieve was at home at the time of my arrival. She introduced me to Elena. Elena was the owner of the offered room. She gave me the keys to the flat, told me the basic instructions and showed the room. I saw immediately that the level of the room is not the same as on the photos of my booked room. The room was full of the things of Elena's son (helmets, toy weapons, etc), console game posters on the wall, etc. The room wasn't clean, the reason of this could be Elena's dog. I didn't refused the room, because I didn't want to look after an other one, but if I were in the same situation again, probably I would try. That time I didn't know but during the night I realized that the mattress of the bed is too soft and really uncomfortable, I woke up many times because of this. The wifi didn't work permanently in the room, as Elena said when I arrived. So the room wasn't good. The bathroom was okay.

Elena was nice as well.

It's a pity that my first occasion with Airbnb was quite bad.

Acceuil trhellos agrhelloable et chaleureux de la part de Lieve, je suis resthello chez Marleen que j'ai rapidement croishello mais qui fut trhellos sympathique de rencontrer.Le logement est conforme aux photos, proche de la gare et des transports en commun.Le seul bhellomol vient du manque de cuisine chez Marleen sinon shellojour trhellos agrhelloable !

Jour de passage, donc pas grand chose hello dire pour une nuit...
Hormis que le lieu est proche de la salle de concert De Roma donc pour moi c'hellotait l'idhelloal. Hhellote et logement convenable.

I recently stayed with them for 5 weeks. The reason I picked there place was: (1) it was located close to the Antwerp train Station, (2) it was the cheapest/or close to it on Airbnb, (3) the good reviews

PROS: 
(1) It is about a 10 minute walk to the Antwerp Train Station. Basically all you do, is get out of their apartment, walk left, and your there. If you keep walking for another 20 minutes, you will be in the heart of Antwerp where all the tourist are. Their neighborhood is in a heavily Moroccan/Turkish part of town. I was ok with it, but some might not be. 
(2) Lieve the wife is an absolute sweet heart. She will give you a map of the city, and while I was there, she would randomly ask how I was doing, and how my day was. She is really sweet + kind. I did not have much conversation with the husband (fronk). 
(3) they are always home! So no matter what time you get to town, you can probably locate them easily. 

CONS: 
(1) The Airbnb advertisement is not correct. They live in a small 3 bedroom apartment. In which, they rent out ALL THREE ROOMS to different people!! Thus their is always people coming and going. Usually both rooms are booked, and they sleep in the 3rd room. However when all 3 are booked, they sleep in the living room. (if I knew they rent out all 3 rooms to different people, i would have never stayed here).  
(2) CLEANLINESS (Huge Problem): They have 2 bathrooms. Their first bathroom has a functioning toilet. The second bathroom has a non-functioning toilet and a shower. Thus all the guest, and the hosts, use the first bathroom (when they have to use the toilet). Whenever I would use the bathroom I would clean the toilet seat with rubbing alcohol, because I found on numerous occasions it to be disgustingly dirty (feces and urine staines). Im not sure if this was from the other guests or the husband. Furthermore, every time you take a shower you have to take out the shower plug, remove the peoples hairs, and then take your shower. There is actually written instruction on the shower how to do this. Thus bring plastic gloves with you! Again, coming from the US, I found this disgusting. Not sure if its a common thing in Europe. In general, the bathroom, shower, and kitchen were not the cleanest as they could be. And sometimes absolutely disgusting. 

ALL IN ALL: if you stay for 1-2 nights its an ok choice (specially given if you don't want to cook, or spend long durations in the apartment). It will get the job done, and you probably won't experience the lack of cleanliness. However if you stay for longer, I strongly suggest you finding another place. OR just renting an apartment month-to-month (for about $600 Euros a month...something that I later learned).

There is not much to add to the other comments. 
Great hosts
Great location
Nice flat
Great balcony 

So I can totally recommend that accommodation!

fields.description:
Location, Location, Location.... as they say.

    Well you would be hard pressed to beat this one !

    Its all here at your doorstep... literally :-)

    Easy access - stroll to everything !

    You will find yourself stepping out and strolling to everything - everywhere - every day. Also easy cab access day and night. Ferry, train or bus options also.

    Whether here for business or pleasure - this is the perfect Sydney 'base'.

    Gorgeous, private, Rocks Village setting. Far enough away from the main tourist hub at Circular Quay to keep it  close enough to enjoy the vibe.

    The Boutique part of the new Rocks/Harbour foreshore precinct !

    Huge selection of Harbour Side Restaurants, Cafes and Bars, Historic Pubs - Shops... all at your doorstep. No more than a 1 min stroll.

fields.context:
NL | Ik heb hier echt met veel plezier verbleven! Hele aardige, warme bewoners. Het ligt aan de grote weg, je kunt makkelijker en snel overal naar toe. Het huis is schoon/proper en je kunt van alle voorzieningen gebruik maken. Het huis en de sfeer is zeer comfortabel. De communicatie verliep vlekkeloos. Hier kom ik nog eens terug als ik naar Antwerpen kom en ik raad iedereen aan om hier te logeren! :) 

ENG |  I stayed here with pleasure. Very lovely and warm residents. The house is on the main road so you can move yourself very quickly and easily. The house itself is very clean and comfortable. You can use all the services. The communication was perfect. I definitely recommend this place and Ihelloll come back in the future when I come to Antwerp! :)
Super hhellotes je recommande vivement. Lieve et Franck sont trhellos sympathiques chaleureux. L'ambiance est apaisante . Je ne pouvais pas trouver mieux.
Everything was good, thank you

fields.context:
Une ambiance dhellotendue et de confiance. Une chouette exphellorience, je recommande !
I was expecting a great airbnb and I was right ! Despite the absence of Fronk and Lieve, I met wonderful people and had interesting talks. I would recommend it to anyone who come to Antwerpen for a short or a long stay.

I loved Ramona's apartment -- the street was quiet and picturesque, reminded me of a quaint street in Paris. It took me less than 15 minutes to get there from Antwerp Centraal Station, and Ramona was there to meet me at the tram stop and show me to her beautiful home. Everything was exactly as described, and I loved how she decorated the walls with little quotes and pictures everywhere. The best part was her bed, where I had two lovely serene nights dreaming before the natural light waking me up in the morning. Thank you so much Ramona, I can only hope my future airbnb experiences are half as wonderful. x x
lovely apartment, very well located. Nice and helpful neighbours!  Was a nice experience.
